1.8.2 Execution Details
Warm-up Period: Every test run included a 2-minute "warm-up" phase to allow for JVM/Python JIT optimization and Kubernetes pod stabilization before data collection.
Cool-down Period: A 1-minute interval was maintained between runs to allow the CPU temperature to normalize and for the cluster to clear any pending network sockets or "Terminating" pods.
Data Aggregation: The final metrics reported in the results section represent the mean values across the 10 runs per category, with P95/P99 latencies calculated to identify outliers and tail-end performance issues.

